      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLAMEITONTHEBOOGIE (3) hasn't raced since finishing third over 1200m at Hobart on December 28. Fitter for a trial win and is unbeaten from two tries fresh. Has never missed the frame in career and expected to go close at return ILOVETHISTOWN (7) had first try this circuit over 1350m last time, finishing 2.25 lengths back in sixth after being handy in the run. Better for the experience and will give a sight again. PLATINUM REGGAE (9) went back early from her wide draw over 1009m at this track last time but hit the line strongly to finish fourth. One to watch for in the closing stages. ZOETE'S ROCK (2) returns from a layoff of ten weeks. Strong record this course and distance and is sure to be ready to run a forward race. ONLY OLD ONCE (8) was safely held fresh but is fitter and can improve sharply.",
